replies.body:
{{champion:43}} 
What she has which other enchanters don't is an AOE mega-shield with mvs, BUT this is the main problem on proplay... Karma has a potential with her early damage, but if she failed in dominance the lane, I feel like later she just has her shield, because if you behind, usually your team is behind and you cannot engage quite good with mvs from shield, especially on soloq, where communication is limited(?)(I can find the right word, sorry >_&lt;). 
I was happy for changes, when they wanted to improve mechanics on W, the idea of cloth-line was interesting, but I was worried with those changes due to the fact giving her reducing cooldowns and refreshing mana skill for allies wouldn't be that good on  not-coordinated teams and could have become OP on proplay, like she used to... So they left it again... I wish she could got even smaller visual update like Ezreal, to match more of her splash arts and improve her gameplay. 
I like she has a lot of ways to play, but I feel like it always end like every of that is way too good or so not worth to even pick her... I often feel I should have pick Morgana, even if I fell off and be behind I still have quite long snear and CC-prevent shield which is always good to have and I can build AP, supportish or even tanky... Or just pick Janna, Lulu or Nami, because usually they are better enchanters and they can poke and deal dmg in lane(not quite high as Karma, but still they are better in late games). 
I love Karma, but seriously, sometimes I feel like I have nothing except shield and just some damage.
{{item:3070}}
